HEADWORD: Bowgrace
<hw>Bow"grace`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A frame or fender of rope or junk, laid out at the sides or bows of
a vessel to secure it from injury by floating ice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

